-- Australian shares to open higher, NZ stocks hit record
-- By Cecile Lefort
-- Tue Nov 18, 2014 04:26PM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Nov 19 (Reuters) - Australian shares should open higher on Wednesday, snapping two straight sessions of declines as investors take heart from an encouraging performance on Wall Street.

The local stock index futures <YAPcm1> gained 0.1 percent to 5,422.0, a 22.3-point premium to the close of the underlying S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO> on Tuesday. Orica <ORI.AX>, the world's largest industrial explosives maker, will release full-year results and is expected to give an update on the sale of its chemicals unit. New Zealand's benchmark NZX 50 index <.NZ50> set a fresh record high of 5,512 in early trade. For a summary of overnight action across global markets, double-click on [AU/CALL].